# Ardatovo, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Ardatovo (; , Ar≈∫at) is a rural locality (a village) in Maxyutovsky Selsoviet, Kugarchinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 191 as of 2010. There are 2 streets.
Geography
Ardatovo is located 50 km south of Mrakovo (the district's administrative centre) by road. Nizhneye Sazovo is the nearest rural locality.
